Gamble v. Queens County Water Co. et al. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. January 28, 1889.) Appeal from special term, New York county. Action-by James Gamble against the Queens County Water Company and others. The defendants appeal from an order granting an injunction.

Argued before' Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Macombeb, JJ.

Hornblower & Byrne, for appellants. Knevals & Perry, for respondent. *956Van Brunt, P. J.

This case must be stricken from the calendar, and cannot be considered by the court, because the record contains no findings signed by the judge. Ordered accordingly. All concur.
